28/09/2003
SARAJEVO, Bosnia and Herzegovina (BiH) -- The delegation of the European Commission in BiH is holding a two-day conference in Sarajevo. 
The forum, sponsored by the Konrad Adenauer Foundation and BiH Prime Minister Adnan Terzic, started on Saturday (27 September). 
Benefits and costs of EU enlargement, as well as preparation of candidate and member countries, are under discussion. 
Representatives of Slovakia, Poland and Hungary presented reports on their experiences with the EU accession in order to help BiH speed up the process, while Deputy High Representative to BiH Werner Wendt said the country should proceed with the EU integration reforms in order to attract foreign investors and to secure employment for its citizens. 
(Onasa, BHTV 1 - 27/09/03)
